        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 6:06PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 606 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles west of Pinon, or 19 miles northwest of Pueblo, moving
northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fountain.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
